---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import HorizontalCard from "../components/HorizontalCard.astro";
---

<BaseLayout sideBarActiveItemID="home" image="/og-home.webp">
  {/* =========================================================
      1. HERO - primary line + identity + contributions deck
      ========================================================= */}
  <div class="pt-5 pb-10">
    <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold leading-tight max-w-3xl">
      The institutional environment around founders matters more than we usually
      admit. I study how, and why.
    </h1>
    <p class="text-lg md:text-xl mt-5 opacity-90 max-w-3xl">
      Chuck Eesley. Professor of Management Science &amp; Engineering, Stanford
      University. Co-director for international entrepreneurship at the Stanford
      Technology Ventures Program (STVP).
    </p>
    <p class="text-base mt-3 opacity-80 max-w-3xl">
      <span class="font-semibold opacity-90">Foundational concepts:</span>
      institutional barriers to entry and growth, institutional inconsistency,
      platforms as private regulators of ventures.
    </p>
    <div class="mt-6 flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a class="btn btn-primary" href="#selected-writing">Read the research ↓</a>
      <a
        class="btn btn-outline"
        href="https://newsletter.chuckeesley.com/subscribe"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
      >
        Substack
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>

  {/* =========================================================
      2. IMPACT BAND - single most legible artifact
      ========================================================= */}
  <section class="mb-14 border-y border-base-300 py-8">
    <div class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.18em] opacity-70 mb-4">Impact</div>
    <p class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold leading-snug max-w-3xl">
      Forty years of Stanford alumni data. ~40,000 active companies. $2.7T in
      annual revenue. 5.4M jobs.
    </p>
    <p class="text-base md:text-lg mt-3 opacity-90 max-w-3xl">
      What a university's institutional environment contributes to
      entrepreneurship, separated from the selection of who walks in the door.
      With William F. Miller.
    </p>
    <p class="text-sm mt-3 opacity-70 max-w-3xl">
      Field research and teaching across six continents, more than 200,000
      students reached through STVP's global programs.
    </p>
    <div class="mt-4 text-sm">
      <a
        class="link"
        href="https://engineering.stanford.edu/news/study-reports-stanford-alumni-create-nearly-3-trillion-economic-impact"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
      >
        Read the study →
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  {/* =========================================================
      3. VALIDATION STRIP - quiet authority, scholarly markers
      ========================================================= */}
  <section class="mb-14">
    <div class="text-sm md:text-base opacity-85 leading-loose">
      <span class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.18em] opacity-60 mr-2"
        >Published in</span
      >
      <span class="font-display italic"
        >Nature · Strategic Management Journal · Organization Science</span
      >
    </div>
    <div class="text-sm md:text-base opacity-85 leading-loose mt-3">
      <span class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.18em] opacity-60 mr-2"
        >Featured in</span
      >
      <span class="font-display italic"
        >World Economic Forum · Bloomberg · Stanford Engineering, The Future of
        Everything</span
      >
    </div>
  </section>

  {/* =========================================================
      4. CURRENTLY - active research signal, out of hero contention
      ========================================================= */}
  <div
    class="mb-14 border-l-4 border-base-300 pl-4 py-1 text-base leading-relaxed opacity-90"
  >
    <span class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.18em] opacity-70 mr-2"
      >Currently</span
    >
    Writing a book on how institutions and policy produce deep-tech founders. Selectively considering additional <a
      class="link"
      href="/board-and-advisory">board, advisory, and consulting engagements</a
    > at the intersection of AI, industrial policy, and entrepreneurship.
  </div>

  {/* =========================================================
      5. SELECTED WRITING - curated five, NAE reader ordering
      ========================================================= */}
  <section id="selected-writing" class="scroll-mt-24">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-2">Selected writing</h2>
    <p class="text-base opacity-80 mb-6 max-w-2xl">
      Peer-reviewed research and policy writing, hand-picked for readers new to
      the work rather than listed by date.
    </p>

    <HorizontalCard
      title="The Algorithmic Financing of Online Misinformation"
      desc="Published in Nature. How programmatic advertising routes money to misinformation sites, and what advertisers can do about it. With Wajeeha Ahmad, Ananya Sen, and Erik Brynjolfsson."
      url="https://doi.org/10.1038/s41586-024-07404-1"
      badge="NATURE"
      target="_blank"
    />
    <div class="divider my-0"></div>
    <HorizontalCard
      title="Stanford Alumni Economic-Impact Study"
      desc="With William F. Miller. Decades of data on how one university produces ventures whose annual revenues rival a top-ten economy."
      url="https://engineering.stanford.edu/news/study-reports-stanford-alumni-create-nearly-3-trillion-economic-impact"
      badge="STUDY"
      target="_blank"
    />
    <div class="divider my-0"></div>
    <HorizontalCard
      title="Export Controls and the Global Reallocation of Venture Capital"
      desc="Working paper. U.S. controls meant to slow China's semiconductor sector coincided with Chinese chip startups raising roughly 12% more, and 6 percentage points more financing."
      url="/research/export-controls-vc"
      badge="WORKING PAPER"
      target="_self"
    />
    <div class="divider my-0"></div>
    <HorizontalCard
      title="The Institutional Layer of an Innovation Economy"
      desc="World Economic Forum, sole-author essay, June 2026. The decisive ingredient is the institutional layer between state spending and market freedom: tech-transfer offices, university-industry programs, accelerators, and founder-mentor networks."
      url="https://www.weforum.org/stories/2026/06/research-ai-innovation-beyond-market-freedom-versus-state-funding/"
      badge="ESSAY"
      target="_blank"
    />
    <div class="divider my-0"></div>
    <HorizontalCard
      title="CHIPS Act and Semiconductor Venture Capital"
      desc="Han and Eesley, working paper. How industrial-policy credibility, not just scale, shapes where private capital actually moves."
      url="/research"
      badge="WORKING PAPER"
      target="_self"
    />

    <div
      class="mt-6 text-sm opacity-80 flex flex-wrap gap-x-6 gap-y-2"
    >
      <a
        class="link"
        href="https://newsletter.chuckeesley.com"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
      >
        More writing on the Substack →
      </a>
      <a class="link" href="/publications">Full publication list →</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  {/* =========================================================
      6. FOOTER UTILITY ROW - demoted links, one home each
      ========================================================= */}
  <div
    class="border-t border-base-300 mt-14 pt-6 text-sm flex flex-wrap gap-x-6 gap-y-2 opacity-80"
  >
    <a class="link" href="/press-kit">Press kit</a>
    <a class="link" href="/board-and-advisory">Board &amp; advisory</a>
    <a class="link" href="/services">Speaking</a>
    <a
      class="link"
      href="https://profiles.stanford.edu/charles-eesley"
      target="_blank"
      rel="noopener noreferrer"
    >
      Stanford profile ↗
    </a>
    <a class="link" href="/cv">Full CV</a>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
